eriment by moving the inclusion's\nlocation $z$ inside $\\Omega$. Finally, using this reconstructed field in the\nLam\\'e PDE system, via a numerical differentiation, we recover the values of\nthe mass density inside $\\Omega$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 7 May 2023 15:55:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 May 2023 08:06:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-25"}
